description: Backend and API service standards for reliability and safety
globs: backend/**/*.{ts,js,py,sql}
alwaysApply: false
---

# Backend Standards

- Keep API handlers thin; place domain logic in services/use-cases.
- Validate all inputs at boundaries and return structured errors.
- Use explicit auth and authorization checks on protected endpoints.
- Treat external integrations (SMS, push, auth) as failure-prone and retry-safe.
- Implement idempotency for operations that can be retried.

# Data and Contracts

- Version database schema changes with clear migration notes.
- Keep API contracts explicit (request/response/error format).
- Do not break existing fields without a migration/deprecation path.
- Enforce limits from PRD (e.g., family member capacity) server-side.

# Security and Operations

- Never hardcode secrets; use environment variables and secure storage.
- Log with correlation IDs for debugging critical flows (SOS, sync, auth).
- Do not log PII in plain text; mask phone numbers and sensitive identifiers.
